<h2>Introduction</h2>

<p>
Congratulations on obtaining your County Court Judgment (CCJ). However, a judgment alone does not automatically result in payment. If the defendant does not pay voluntarily within the time specified by the court, you will need to take <strong>enforcement action</strong> to recover the money owed.
</p>

<p>
This guide explains the main enforcement methods available in England, the costs involved, and how to choose the most appropriate method based on your circumstances.
</p>

